# Antigravity Assistant Rules — Mtn Elite One Project

[GLOBAL_CONTEXT]
- Project Nature: Official Digital Platform for Cameroonian Football (MTN Elite One).
- Architecture: Feature-Based Monorepo (NestJS Backend / React 18 Frontend)[cite: 1].
- Quality Standard: No 'any' type allowed. Strict TypeScript compliance[cite: 1].

[FRONTEND_COMPLETION_RULES]
- UI Components: Never generate generic administrative tables or default gray SaaS dashboards[cite: 1].
- Responsiveness: Enforce Tailwind prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:) for layout components to support 320px up to 1920px viewpoints[cite: 1].
- Data Fetching: Prohibit direct useEffect for REST calls. Auto-suggest TanStack Query (@tanstack/react-query) custom hooks hooks.
- Accessibility: Automatically inject 'aria-live="polite"' on real-time match events or match score views updated via WebSockets[cite: 1, 1]. All club/player images must strictly feature an descriptive 'alt' tag[cite: 1].

[BACKEND_COMPLETION_RULES]
- Data Integrity: Ensure DTOs use 'class-validator' decorators for incoming controller payloads.
- Database Contract: Match PostgreSQL entities (TypeORM) structure with the shared TypeScript interfaces on the frontend.
- CMS Management: Editorial modules, Match reports, and Culture stories must output structured HTML/JSON nodes compatible with a Tiptap rich text layout[cite: 1].